== Births == * {{ill|Kankō|ja|Kankō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1009]] [[December 14]]) – Emperor Go-Suzaku, the 69th Emperor of Japan (d. [[1045]]). * {{ill|Bunroku|ja|Bunroku|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1594]] [[January 6]]) – Maeda Toshitsune, the 3rd lord of the Kaga Domain (d. [[1658]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|Bunsei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1820]] [[January 10]]) – Ando Nobumasa, a Rōjū and the 5th lord of Iwaki-Heiban in Mutsu Province (d. [[1871]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[January 15]]) – Sakai Toshihiko, a socialist activist (d. [[1933]]). * Meiji 5th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[December 25]]) – Soeda Asenbō, an enka singer (d. [[1944]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1576]] [[December 15]]) – Kitabatake Tomonori, the 8th head of the Kitabatake family and governor of Ise (born [[1528]]). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|Kan'ei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 19th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1643]] [[January 15]]) – Tachibana Muneshige, lord of the Tanakura Domain and the Yanagawa Domain (born [[1567]] or [[1569]]). * [[Hōreki]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1755]] [[January 7]]) – Nabeshima Muneshige, lord of the Saga Domain (born [[1687]]).
