'''November 25''' is the 25th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11th Month (Old Calendar)|1=November (Lunisolar)|2=ja|3=11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|qq=}} of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|qq=}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|Taian|qq=}}.

== Events ==
* [[初始]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[9]] [[January 10]]) – In the 1st year of [[Wang Mang]], he founded the Xin dynasty, leading to the fall of the Former Han.
* [[養和]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1182]] [[January 1]]) – Empress Heitokuko of [[Emperor Takakura]] was granted an honorary title, becoming known as Kenreimonin, as decreed in the "Meigetsuki" on January 1.
* {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|Kenkyū|qq=}} 3rd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1192]] [[December 31]]) – Military commander [[Kumagai Naomitsu]] became a monk, joined [[Hōnen]], and took the name Renshō.
* [[Kōji (Muromachi period)|Kōji]] 3rd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1557]] [[December 15]]) – [[Mōri Motonari]] recorded 14 precepts for his sons [[Mōri Takamoto]], [[Yoshikawa Motoharu]], and [[Kobayakawa Takakage]], later remembered as the story of "Three Arrows."
* {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|Jōkyō|qq=}} 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1687]] [[December 29]]) – [[Matsuo Bashō]] departed on his journey as described in "Oku no Komon," famously beginning with "I shall be known as the traveler."

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kankō|ja|Kankō|qq=}} 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1009]] [[December 14]]) – Emperor Go-Suzaku, the 69th Emperor of Japan (d. [[1045]]).
* {{ill|Bunroku|ja|Bunroku|qq=}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1594]] [[January 6]]) – Maeda Toshitsune, the 3rd lord of the Kaga Domain (d. [[1658]]).
* {{ill|Bunsei|ja|Bunsei|qq=}} 2nd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1820]] [[January 10]]) – Ando Nobumasa, a Rōjū and the 5th lord of Iwaki-Heiban in Mutsu Province (d. [[1871]]).
* [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1871]] [[January 15]]) – Sakai Toshihiko, a socialist activist (d. [[1933]]).
* Meiji 5th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1872]] [[December 25]]) – Soeda Asenbō, an enka singer (d. [[1944]]).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|qq=}} 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[1576]] [[December 15]]) – Kitabatake Tomonori, the 8th head of the Kitabatake family and governor of Ise (born [[1528]]).
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|Kan'ei|qq=}} 19th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1643]] [[January 15]]) – Tachibana Muneshige, lord of the Tanakura Domain and the Yanagawa Domain (born [[1567]] or [[1569]]).
* [[Hōreki]] 4th year ([[Gregorian calendar]] [[1755]] [[January 7]]) – Nabeshima Muneshige, lord of the Saga Domain (born [[1687]]).

