== Events == * [[初始]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:9|9]] [[:en:January 10|January 10]]) – In the 1st year of [[Wang Mang]], he founded the Xin dynasty, leading to the fall of the Former Han. * [[:en:養和|養和]] 1st year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1182|1182]] [[:en:January 1|January 1]]) – Empress Heitokuko of [[:en:Emperor Takakura|Emperor Takakura]] was granted an honorary title, becoming known as Kenreimonin, as decreed in the "Meigetsuki" on January 1. * {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|Kenkyū|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenkyū|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 3rd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1192|1192]] [[:en:December 31|December 31]]) – Military commander [[Kumagai Naomitsu]] became a monk, joined [[:en:Hōnen|Hōnen]], and took the name Renshō. * [[Kōji (Muromachi period)|Kōji]] 3rd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1557|1557]] [[:en:December 15|December 15]]) – [[Mōri Motonari]] recorded 14 precepts for his sons [[Mōri Takamoto]], [[Yoshikawa Motoharu]], and [[Kobayakawa Takakage]], later remembered as the story of "Three Arrows." * {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|Jōkyō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōkyō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1687|1687]] [[:en:December 29|December 29]]) – [[Matsuo Bashō]] departed on his journey as described in "Oku no Komon," famously beginning with "I shall be known as the traveler."
== Births == * {{ill|Kankō|ja|Kankō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kankō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 6th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1009|1009]] [[:en:December 14|December 14]]) – Emperor Go-Suzaku, the 69th Emperor of Japan (d. [[:en:1045|1045]]). * {{ill|Bunroku|ja|Bunroku|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunroku|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1594|1594]] [[:en:January 6|January 6]]) – Maeda Toshitsune, the 3rd lord of the Kaga Domain (d. [[:en:1658|1658]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|Bunsei|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunsei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1820|1820]] [[:en:January 10|January 10]]) – Ando Nobumasa, a Rōjū and the 5th lord of Iwaki-Heiban in Mutsu Province (d. [[:en:1871|1871]]). * [[Meiji era|Meiji]] 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1871|1871]] [[:en:January 15|January 15]]) – Sakai Toshihiko, a socialist activist (d. [[:en:1933|1933]]). * Meiji 5th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1872|1872]] [[:en:December 25|December 25]]) – Soeda Asenbō, an enka singer (d. [[:en:1944|1944]]).
== Deaths == * {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 4th year ([[Julian calendar]] [[:en:1576|1576]] [[:en:December 15|December 15]]) – Kitabatake Tomonori, the 8th head of the Kitabatake family and governor of Ise (born [[:en:1528|1528]]). * {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|Kan'ei|qq=|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kan'ei|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 19th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1643|1643]] [[:en:January 15|January 15]]) – Tachibana Muneshige, lord of the Tanakura Domain and the Yanagawa Domain (born [[:en:1567|1567]] or [[:en:1569|1569]]). * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1755|1755]] [[:en:January 7|January 7]]) – Nabeshima Muneshige, lord of the Saga Domain (born [[:en:1687|1687]]).
