'''November 25''' is the 25th day of the month {{ill|November (Lunisolar)|ja|11th Month (Old Calendar)|1=November (Lunisolar)|2=ja|3=11月 (旧暦)|lt=November (Shimotsuki)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|13=User:Immanuelle/November (Lunisolar)|qq=}} of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|Old Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|Rokuyō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|Taian|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taian|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.

== Events ==
* [[初始]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|9|en|9|WD=Q19108|lt=9|1=9}} {{ill|January 10|en|January 10|WD=Q2243|lt=January 10|1=January 10}}) – In the 1st year of {{ill|Wang Mang|en|Wang Mang|WD=Q7250|lt=Wang Mang|1=Wang Mang}}, he founded the Xin dynasty, leading to the fall of the Former Han.
* [[:en:養和|養和]] 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1182|en|1182|WD=Q19708|lt=1182|1=1182}} {{ill|January 1|en|January 1|WD=Q2150|lt=January 1|1=January 1}}) – Empress Heitokuko of {{ill|Emperor Takakura|en|Emperor Takakura|WD=Q357261|lt=Emperor Takakura|1=Emperor Takakura}} was granted an honorary title, becoming known as Kenreimonin, as decreed in the "Meigetsuki" on January 1.
* {{ill|Kenkyū|ja|Kenkyū|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kenkyū|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1192|en|1192|WD=Q19739|lt=1192|1=1192}} {{ill|December 31|en|December 31|WD=Q2912|lt=December 31|1=December 31}}) – Military commander [[Kumagai Naomitsu]] became a monk, joined {{ill|Hōnen|en|Hōnen|WD=Q507980|lt=Hōnen|1=Hōnen}}, and took the name Renshō.
* {{ill|Kōji (Muromachi period)|en|Kōji (Muromachi period)|WD=Q1143910|lt=Kōji|1=Kōji (Muromachi period)}} 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1557|en|1557|WD=Q6595|lt=1557|1=1557}} {{ill|December 15|en|December 15|WD=Q2383|lt=December 15|1=December 15}}) – {{ill|Mōri Motonari|en|Mōri Motonari|WD=Q1156545|lt=Mōri Motonari|1=Mōri Motonari}} recorded 14 precepts for his sons {{ill|Mōri Takamoto|en|Mōri Takamoto|WD=Q859795|lt=Mōri Takamoto|1=Mōri Takamoto}}, [[Yoshikawa Motoharu]], and {{ill|Kobayakawa Takakage|en|Kobayakawa Takakage|WD=Q1143508|lt=Kobayakawa Takakage|1=Kobayakawa Takakage}}, later remembered as the story of "Three Arrows."
* {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|Jōkyō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōkyō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1687|en|1687|WD=Q7668|lt=1687|1=1687}} {{ill|December 29|en|December 29|WD=Q2862|lt=December 29|1=December 29}}) – {{ill|Matsuo Bashō|en|Matsuo Bashō|WD=Q5676|lt=Matsuo Bashō|1=Matsuo Bashō}} departed on his journey as described in "Oku no Komon," famously beginning with "I shall be known as the traveler."

== Births ==
* {{ill|Kankō|ja|Kankō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kankō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 6th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1009|en|1009|WD=Q19236|lt=1009|1=1009}} {{ill|December 14|en|December 14|WD=Q2382|lt=December 14|1=December 14}}) – Emperor Go-Suzaku, the 69th Emperor of Japan (d. {{ill|1045|en|1045|WD=Q19351|lt=1045|1=1045}}).
* [[Bunroku]]{{efn|Period of Japanese history (1592–1596)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunroku|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1594|en|1594|WD=Q6777|lt=1594|1=1594}} {{ill|January 6|en|January 6|WD=Q2221|lt=January 6|1=January 6}}) – Maeda Toshitsune, the 3rd lord of the Kaga Domain (d. {{ill|1658|en|1658|WD=Q6991|lt=1658|1=1658}}).
* {{ill|Bunsei|ja|Bunsei|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Bunsei|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 2nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1820|en|1820|WD=Q6973|lt=1820|1=1820}} {{ill|January 10|en|January 10|WD=Q2243|lt=January 10|1=January 10}}) – Ando Nobumasa, a Rōjū and the 5th lord of Iwaki-Heiban in Mutsu Province (d. {{ill|1871|en|1871|WD=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}}).
* {{ill|Meiji era|en|Meiji era|WD=Q3125096|lt=Meiji|1=Meiji era}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1871|en|1871|WD=Q7746|lt=1871|1=1871}} {{ill|January 15|en|January 15|WD=Q2260|lt=January 15|1=January 15}}) – Sakai Toshihiko, a socialist activist (d. {{ill|1933|en|1933|WD=Q18726|lt=1933|1=1933}}).
* Meiji 5th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1872|en|1872|WD=Q7753|lt=1872|1=1872}} {{ill|December 25|en|December 25|WD=Q2745|lt=December 25|1=December 25}}) – Soeda Asenbō, an enka singer (d. {{ill|1944|en|1944|WD=Q5268|lt=1944|1=1944}}).

== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Tenshō|ja|Tenshō|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 4th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|WD=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1576|en|1576|WD=Q6700|lt=1576|1=1576}} {{ill|December 15|en|December 15|WD=Q2383|lt=December 15|1=December 15}}) – Kitabatake Tomonori, the 8th head of the Kitabatake family and governor of Ise (born {{ill|1528|en|1528|WD=Q6415|lt=1528|1=1528}}).
* {{ill|Kan'ei|ja|Kan'ei|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kan'ei|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 19th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1643|en|1643|WD=Q6917|lt=1643|1=1643}} {{ill|January 15|en|January 15|WD=Q2260|lt=January 15|1=January 15}}) – Tachibana Muneshige, lord of the Tanakura Domain and the Yanagawa Domain (born {{ill|1567|en|1567|WD=Q6642|lt=1567|1=1567}} or {{ill|1569|en|1569|WD=Q6653|lt=1569|1=1569}}).
* {{ill|Hōreki|en|Hōreki|WD=Q1194397|lt=Hōreki|1=Hōreki}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|WD=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1755|en|1755|WD=Q7627|lt=1755|1=1755}} {{ill|January 7|en|January 7|WD=Q2228|lt=January 7|1=January 7}}) – Nabeshima Muneshige, lord of the Saga Domain (born {{ill|1687|en|1687|WD=Q7668|lt=1687|1=1687}}).

